OL,3,CInquest opens into death of man
OL,4,Cfatally crushed in hospital car park
OL,6,FThe coroner heard that the driver of
OL,7,Fthe vehicle lost control as he
OL,8,Freversed, moving backwards and hitting
OL,9,FMr Burton.JOpening the inquest into
OL,10,Fhis death at the Berkshire Coroners'
OL,11,FOffice today, Tuesday 23 April,
OL,12,Fassistant Coroner Ian Wade said the
OL,13,Fincident was "tragic and very
OL,14,Fpoignant."JHe said: "In the course of
OL,15,Fvisiting a friend who was an in-
OL,16,Fpatient at the Royal Berkshire
OL,17,FHospital on March 13 this year,
OL,18,FRichard Burton was guiding a friend to
OL,19,Fbe able to park a Mitsubishi 44 SUV
OL,20,Fwhen, unaccountably, the driver lost
OL,21,Fcontrol of the vehicle and collided
OL,22,Fwith Richard in the car park - causing
OL,23,Fserious and fatal crush injuries."
